Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp}, a big
pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and
cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch
of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and cook, stirring often, until fragrant and lightly
browned, ~{2-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over
with @Turkish spice blend{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken
in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

== Gremolata ==

While chicken cooks, add @dried apricots{1%ounce}(chopped), scallion greens,
lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice, a large drizzle of olive oil, and a pinch of
salt and pepper to bowl with almonds; stir to combine. Set aside.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @hummus{4%tbsp}, @yogurt{4%tbsp}, a squeeze of
lemon juice, a drizzle of olive oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper until smooth.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice, carrots, and chicken between #bowls{} in separate sections. Drizzle with
hummus sauce. Top with gremolata. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.